1]Binary Search is a searching technique used on a sorted array.
Instead of checking every element one by one, it repeatedly divides the search space into half.

2]We can use binary search when the array is sorted.

3. Time Complexity

Linear Search	O(n)
Binary Search	O(log n)

4. basic binary search code
int binarySearch(vector<int>& nums, int target)
{
    int low = 0;
    int high = nums.size() - 1;

    while(low <= high)
    {
        int mid = low + (high - low) / 2;

        if(nums[mid] == target)
            return mid;

        else if(nums[mid] < target)
            low = mid + 1;

        else
            high = mid - 1;
    }

    return -1;
}


5]Use: mid = low + (high-low)/2; to avoid integer overflow.

